# Bun Preference

Default to Bun over Node.js/npm toolchain.

## Commands
- `bun <file>` not `node`/`ts-node`
- `bun install` not `npm install`/`yarn`/`pnpm`
- `bun run <script>` not `npm run`
- `bunx <package>` not `npx`
- `bun test` not `jest`/`vitest`
- `bun build` not `webpack`/`esbuild`/`vite`

## Built-in APIs (avoid extra deps)
- `Bun.serve()` - WebSockets, HTTPS, routes (not `express`)
- `bun:sqlite` (not `better-sqlite3`)
- `Bun.file` (not `node:fs` readFile/writeFile)
- `Bun.$` (not `execa`)
- `WebSocket` built-in (not `ws`)
- Auto-loads `.env` (no `dotenv` needed)

## Testing
```ts
import { test, expect } from "bun:test";
test("example", () => expect(1).toBe(1));
```

## Frontend
HTML imports work with Bun.serve() - imports `.tsx`/`.jsx` directly, no build step. Use `bun --hot ./index.ts` for dev. Docs: `node_modules/bun-types/docs/**.mdx`
